The paper deals with the problem of universal compression, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves studying the redundancy of encoding strings generated by iid sampling, which is a problem in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper uses mathematical analysis to derive results, which falls under the category of theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the applications of universal compression, which includes language modeling and insurance, falling under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and social and information networks (cs.SI), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the properties of a set of distributions, which is a problem in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
